ZH: 今天晚上吃了一些点心。
EN: I had some dim sum for dinner tonight.

ZH: 我最喜欢吃虾饺这种点心。
EN: I love eating har gow, it's my favorite dim sum.

ZH: 她会做一个星期一次点心。
EN: She makes dim sum once a week.

ZH: 请问你们想尝尝我们的点心吗？
EN: Would you like to try some of our dim sum?

ZH: 外面买的点心要比自己做的好多了。
EN: Store-bought dim sum tastes much better than homemade.

ZH: 在这家餐馆，点心不太贵。
EN: Dim sum is not too expensive at this restaurant.

ZH: 他们家的烧卖是最棒的点心之一。
EN: Their siu mai is one of the best dim sum dishes.

ZH: 你有没有吃过芋头包这种点心？
EN: Have you ever tried yam buns as dim sum?

ZH: 昨天我去了一个新的点心店。
EN: I went to a new dim sum restaurant yesterday.

ZH: 奶奶经常下午请我们吃点心。
EN: Grandma often treats us to dim sum in the afternoon.

ZH: 这家餐馆的炸春卷是我的最爱点心。
EN: The fried spring rolls at this restaurant are my favorite dim sum.

ZH: 看看这些点心的颜色和形状。
EN: Look at the colors and shapes of these dim sum.

ZH: 他喜欢吃素黄金包这种甜点心。
EN: He enjoys eating custard buns as sweet dim sum.

ZH: 家里人周末总是一起吃点心。
EN: My family always eats dim sum together on weekends.

ZH: 这道点心的味道有点太甜了。
EN: This dim sum dish is a bit too sweet for my taste.

ZH: 你可以尝尝这种传统点心。
EN: You should try this traditional dim sum.

ZH: 我会尝试做一些自制点心。
EN: I will try making some homemade dim sum.

ZH: 这个点心摊卖的各种点心都很好吃。
EN: The dim sum sold at this stall are all very delicious.

ZH: 每个星期天我们都去吃一顿点心。
EN: We go out for dim sum every Sunday.

ZH: 对不起，我今天没时间做点心。
EN: Sorry, I don't have time to make dim sum today.
